while statement is entry-controlled statement .
It first checks the condition and then execute the statement, the process gets continued until the condition becomes false.
The syntax of while loop in c language is given below:
while(condition)
{
Statement
}
Example:
To print numbers from 1 to 5
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
  int i = 1;
    
  while (i <= 5) {
    printf("%d\n", i);
    ++i;
  }

  return 0;
}
